      "sha256": "d2243f3fc6876562b42d1538de903a5ad88e54c798335e83aa7db49339569995",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "[Po79] Pomerance, Carl, The prime number graph. Math. Comp. (1979), 399-408."
    },
    "remarks": {
      "sha256": "727ec9deafec7c768acee0787d1a24f25edea359e2c774883533109713d62440",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "Pomerance \\cite{Po79} has proved the $\\limsup$ is at least $2$."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "a44cee808e540406f339f48b3b803ad0cbc0e641c5433a040d5b1712ea3cf67c",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Let\\[f(n) = \\min_{i<n} (p_{n+i}+p_{n-i}),\\]where $p_k$ is the $k$th prime. Is it true that\\[\\limsup_n (f(n)-2p_n)=\\infty?\\]"
    }
  },
